question.description:
Post-election reversals are rare but high-impact, signaling severe procedural disputes or legal instability.

question.resolution_criteria: This question resolves as “Yes” if, before May 1, 2026, a court or the competent electoral authority nullifies the overall election outcome or orders a re-run that changes which party controls the Tobago House of Assembly. Otherwise resolve “No”. The question resolves using credible sources per https://www.metaculus.com/faq/#definitions.
question.fine_print: Recounts that confirm the same outcome do not count. “Overturned” is defined as an authoritative action that changes the controlling party or invalidates the election wholesale. Candidate Sources (background on the election): https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2026_Tobago_House_of_Assembly_election.
